🔥 What is Java Collections Framework?
The Java Collections Framework (JCF) is a set of classes and interfaces in Java that helps you store, manage, and manipulate
groups of data (objects) efficiently.
👉 Instead of writing your own data structures (like arrays, linked lists), Java already provides ready-made ones.

